WEBVTT

00:03.138 --> 00:06.402
Welcome to the Life Church Podcast.

00:06.422 --> 00:11.568
We are an Acts 2 42 community, a family on a mission to bring a life of Jesus to warranty.

00:13.130 --> 00:17.495
We hope you're ready to hear what God has to say to you today through His Word and by His Spirit.

00:20.939 --> 00:25.304
We are in a series called The Roman Road where we're looking at what salvation means.

00:25.764 --> 00:27.586
We've already had two excellent sessions.

00:28.327 --> 00:30.610
Jeremy started us off.

00:30.722 --> 00:31.944
pointed out the problem.

00:32.465 --> 00:34.167
Jeremy's session was session.

00:34.268 --> 00:35.329
It sounds like seminars.

00:35.930 --> 00:39.015
Jeremy talked about the fact that all have sinned.

00:39.616 --> 00:40.297
All have sinned.

00:40.517 --> 00:42.821
There isn't anyone who can say, nah, I'm all right.

00:43.202 --> 00:43.883
All have sinned.

00:44.423 --> 00:46.046
And that was very clear from Scripture.

00:46.166 --> 00:51.715
And then Helen took us through Christ died for our sins last week.

00:51.735 --> 00:53.778
So we are working through

00:53.858 --> 00:58.386
kind of working through the book of Romans and looking at what salvation means to us.

00:58.667 --> 01:02.494
And today we're looking at confess and believe.

01:03.115 --> 01:05.058
Confess and believe.

01:05.359 --> 01:07.222
I want to read you some scripture before we start.

01:09.947 --> 01:12.332
And I didn't put it on the screen because I want you to just listen to me.

01:14.977 --> 01:16.880
It sounds a bit attention-seeking, doesn't it?

01:16.900 --> 01:18.002
We just listen to me.

01:18.530 --> 01:20.112
But I do want you to just listen to me.

01:20.132 --> 01:23.095
There will be some scripture on the screen later, but I want you to just listen to this.

01:23.135 --> 01:24.277
It's Romans chapter 10.

01:25.558 --> 01:29.042
And Paul is writing to the Romans, and he's expressing.

01:29.503 --> 01:33.848
In fact, Romans is some of Paul's best stuff, yeah?

01:33.868 --> 01:34.188
I think.

01:34.509 --> 01:36.031
Romans is some of Paul's best stuff.

01:36.071 --> 01:42.258
I think one of the reasons Romans is some of Paul's best stuff is because Paul was writing to people he didn't know.

01:42.786 --> 01:48.175
When he writes to the Ephesians, when he writes to the Philippians, he writes to the Galatians, these are all churches that he knows.

01:48.495 --> 01:49.657
These are people that he knows.

01:49.957 --> 01:51.400
He knows what's happening in their lives.

01:51.600 --> 01:53.062
He knows what's happening in their churches.

01:53.363 --> 01:55.486
And so there is more of a focus to those letters.

01:55.827 --> 01:58.050
But to the Romans, Paul didn't know these people.

01:58.391 --> 02:03.058
And so it's like, I'm going to write to you Christians in Rome, and I'm going to give you my best stuff.

02:03.234 --> 02:04.776
because I don't know what's happening in your lives.

02:05.056 --> 02:05.918
I don't know where you are.

02:06.138 --> 02:15.110
So I'm going to make this make as much sense as far as the gospel is concerned so that even though you don't know me and even though I've not met you, you will understand.

02:15.150 --> 02:18.495
At the end of this letter, you will understand what the gospel is all about.

02:19.136 --> 02:23.502
And so Paul writes to the Romans and he expresses lots of incredible things.

02:23.882 --> 02:26.746
If you've not read the book of Romans, can I encourage you to read the book of Romans?

02:27.107 --> 02:27.667
Half an hour.

02:27.727 --> 02:28.609
Take a half an hour.

02:29.049 --> 02:29.830
Maybe this afternoon.

02:29.870 --> 02:30.752
Have a little go.

02:30.792 --> 02:32.594
Yeah.

02:33.154 --> 02:35.279
I will check next week.

02:35.420 --> 02:36.803
There'll be a clipboard at the door.

02:38.627 --> 02:51.058
Romans 10, so Paul is writing about the children of Israel, the Israelites, and he's saying, brothers, my heart's desire and prayer to God for them, the children of Israel, the people who were Israelites, is that they may be saved.

02:51.330 --> 02:55.675
For I bear them witness that they have a zeal for God, but not according to knowledge.

02:55.695 --> 02:59.399
They're excited and enthusiastic about God, but not according to knowledge.

02:59.419 --> 03:05.745
For being ignorant of the righteousness of God and seeking to establish their own, they did not submit to God's righteousness.

03:06.106 --> 03:10.330
For Christ is the end of the law for righteousness to everyone who believes.

03:10.951 --> 03:16.337
For Moses writes about the righteousness that is based on the law, that the person who does the commandment should live by them.

03:16.557 --> 03:21.202
But righteousness based on faith says, do not say in your heart who will ascend into heaven.

03:21.346 --> 03:22.668
That is to bring Christ down.

03:22.808 --> 03:24.330
Or who will descend into the abyss?

03:24.690 --> 03:26.292
That is to bring Christ up from the dead.

03:26.612 --> 03:27.533
But what does it say?

03:27.574 --> 03:31.638
The word is near you, in your mouth and in your heart.

03:31.759 --> 03:33.941
That is the word of faith that we proclaim.

03:34.382 --> 03:44.594
Because if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

03:45.058 --> 03:50.426
For with the heart one believes and is justified and with the mouth one confesses and is saved.

03:50.766 --> 03:54.732
For the scripture says, everyone who believes in him will not be put to shame.

03:55.092 --> 04:02.002
For there is no distinction between Jew and Greek, for the same Lord is Lord of all, bestowing his riches on all who call on him.

04:02.443 --> 04:07.470
For everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

04:08.071 --> 04:13.298
Everyone who calls on the name of the Lord will be saved.

04:13.954 --> 04:17.342
Our key verse for this morning is Romans 10, 9.

04:17.422 --> 04:28.246
If you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

04:28.266 --> 04:30.691
We could pray there, but we're not going to, we're going to go on.

04:31.373 --> 04:33.618
I think the word confess there is

04:34.370 --> 04:35.832
is not particularly helpful.

04:35.892 --> 04:38.055
And let me say why the word confess is not helpful.

04:38.376 --> 04:44.685
Because I think when we hear the word confess in today's day and age, we're thinking of admitting to something that's wrong.

04:45.225 --> 04:49.572
Yeah, let me admit to something that's wrong and give you an example of what that means.

04:49.792 --> 04:51.935
This week, I annoyed my wife.

04:52.215 --> 04:52.636
Yeah, I know.

04:52.656 --> 04:54.559
You're looking at me like, that's not possible, Nick.

04:54.919 --> 04:55.961
Some of you are looking at me like that.

04:55.981 --> 04:59.085
And some of you are like, yeah, Nick, it rains a lot in the UK.

04:59.145 --> 04:59.686
So what?

04:59.706 --> 05:01.609
It's the same kind of thing, Nick annoyed his wife.

05:01.649 --> 05:02.610
We were in London.

05:02.690 --> 05:05.675
And we're starting a train station.

05:06.916 --> 05:16.531
And I read something that said, if a stranger sits next to you, keep a straight face, look straight ahead and say, did you bring the money?

05:18.754 --> 05:22.120
So I showed it to Lisa, and we both laughed at it because it's quite funny.

05:22.620 --> 05:24.503
And then someone sat next to Lisa.

05:26.446 --> 05:29.010
And I whispered to Lisa, did you bring the money?

05:29.698 --> 05:31.361
She did a lot of giggle, that was fine.

05:31.401 --> 05:38.752
We were reading, we carried on the stranger left, someone else sat to Lisa, sat next to Lisa, and I whispered again, did you bring the money?

05:39.733 --> 05:44.781
Lisa smiled, and then the person left, and I thought this is great, but actually I'm a little bit too quiet.

05:47.846 --> 05:53.895
So from that point, every time someone sat next to Lisa, I was saying did you bring the money, but I was getting louder and louder.

05:54.376 --> 05:55.858
Did you bring the money?

05:56.354 --> 05:58.696
And then he got to the point where someone sat next to Lisa.

05:58.817 --> 06:00.799
I didn't say anything, but Lisa just glared at me.

06:01.419 --> 06:03.301
She just turned and glared.

06:03.862 --> 06:08.166
So I confess that this week I annoyed my wife.

06:08.787 --> 06:10.448
I'm admitting to something that I did.

06:10.929 --> 06:13.371
I'm not asking for your forgiveness, because it was great.

06:13.672 --> 06:18.096
But I'm admitting to something that I did.

06:18.657 --> 06:23.762
That's how we sometimes feel the connotations of the word confess.

06:23.938 --> 06:27.784
But this word actually would be better I think if it was declare.

06:27.824 --> 06:32.812
And actually the word does mean confess and it also does mean declare.

06:33.333 --> 06:36.858
If you declare with your mouth the Lord Jesus.

06:37.399 --> 06:41.005
If you declare with your mouth that Jesus is Lord.

06:41.365 --> 06:46.834
What Paul is saying here to us is this, God is not looking for anonymous Christians.

06:48.162 --> 06:52.970
God is not looking for people who have some kind of conviction in their heart.

06:52.990 --> 06:53.992
Yeah, I follow Jesus.

06:54.072 --> 06:59.882
Yeah, but I have never said it out loud and I have never admitted to it and I've never declared it out loud.

07:00.222 --> 07:10.900
The Bible says, if you declare with your mouth, if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord, there is an expectation that this is not something that we hide from.

07:11.261 --> 07:13.304
This is something that we speak up about.

07:13.504 --> 07:14.546
I'm not asking.

07:14.690 --> 07:22.061
I'm not asking you to just pause tomorrow at work and stand up and say, excuse me, everyone, I just want you to know that Jesus is Lord.

07:22.202 --> 07:25.126
I mean, if you feel you need to do that, that would be amazing.

07:25.847 --> 07:27.350
I'm not asking you to do that.

07:27.370 --> 07:32.397
But what I'm pointing out is scripture says, if we declare with our mouth that Jesus is Lord.

07:32.758 --> 07:40.710
And so there needs to be a conviction and expectation in our hearts that recognizes that being a Christian is not something that we shy away from.

07:40.730 --> 07:43.154
It's not something that we hide.

07:43.330 --> 07:45.793
This is just personal to me.

07:46.273 --> 07:47.455
It's not personal to you.

07:47.815 --> 07:48.716
It is public.

07:49.817 --> 07:54.602
The point of baptism when we have baptism is a public declaration of our faith.

07:55.363 --> 07:57.245
We go through the waters of baptism.

07:57.566 --> 08:03.192
It's kind of like our old lives are being buried and then we're raised again into new life with Jesus.

08:03.252 --> 08:04.413
That's what baptism is.

08:05.354 --> 08:10.119
And after that, it doesn't mean that we don't talk about Jesus ever again.

08:10.139 --> 08:10.940
I've been baptized.

08:11.000 --> 08:11.321
That's it.

08:11.341 --> 08:11.641
I'm done.

08:11.681 --> 08:12.562
I've done the thing.

08:12.770 --> 08:14.753
I went through the waters, I've done the thing.

08:15.014 --> 08:26.233
No, there needs to be, there needs to be those opportunities where we speak about Jesus, where we admit that we, we admit, where we declare that we are people who follow Jesus.

08:27.114 --> 08:38.674
And maybe, just so you know, I don't tend to say that I'm a Christian, I tend to say I'm a Jesus follower, because sometimes Christian means lots of things to different people, but I wanna be clear,

08:38.914 --> 08:40.075
I am following Jesus.

08:40.596 --> 08:41.697
I'm a Jesus follower.

08:41.757 --> 08:45.240
And if that sounds odd, it sounds odd, but that's who I am and that's what I do.

08:45.420 --> 08:46.501
I'm a Jesus follower.

08:46.521 --> 08:47.883
I'm a follower of Jesus.

08:48.603 --> 08:53.228
And maybe in your conversations this week, it might be good to drop that in.

08:53.868 --> 08:56.331
Just by the way, I'm a Jesus follower.

08:56.371 --> 09:00.275
Why do we find it so hard to admit that we are Christians?

09:00.335 --> 09:03.217
Why do we find it so hard to say that sometimes?

09:03.317 --> 09:04.599
Is it a fear of rejection?

09:05.520 --> 09:08.082
Are we worried about what people will think about us?

09:08.322 --> 09:11.466
Are we worried about maybe we'll have some persecution?

09:13.209 --> 09:14.410
Does that really matter?

09:14.450 --> 09:18.156
And does that compare to the truth of knowing who Jesus is?

09:19.097 --> 09:19.918
I don't think it does.

09:19.978 --> 09:25.526
If we declare with our mouths that Jesus is Lord.

09:26.647 --> 09:30.893
Jesus is Lord is a fun phrase, isn't it?

09:30.913 --> 09:31.915
We sang it this morning.

09:31.955 --> 09:33.697
He is Lord, Lord of all.

09:33.978 --> 09:37.202
And it was a great moment as we were singing that together.

09:37.314 --> 09:40.339
What do you think that means that Jesus is Lord?

09:40.699 --> 09:45.868
The word Lord means master or ruler or someone who owns something.

09:46.449 --> 09:54.081
So when you say Jesus is Lord and when I say Jesus is Lord, the words that we're saying are He is my master.

09:54.862 --> 09:56.064
He is my ruler.

09:56.104 --> 09:58.428
I belong to Him.

09:59.770 --> 10:04.978
Now those are words that we can say and it's quite easy to say words.

10:05.218 --> 10:09.343
But does our life reflect the fact that we belong to Him?

10:10.144 --> 10:14.350
Does our life reflect the fact that we belong to Him?

10:16.733 --> 10:18.895
Apparently, did some little bit of research.

10:19.016 --> 10:22.780
Apparently, back in the days, the Knights Templar, sounds great, doesn't it?

10:22.800 --> 10:28.528
The Knights Templar, before they went out to battle, they would have a kind of a church service and they would be baptized.

10:29.128 --> 10:33.554
So these knights with their armor would get into the river and the priesthood pray over them.

10:34.370 --> 10:40.598
But the fascinating thing about that is they would all get into the water and they would submerge themselves except their swords.

10:40.878 --> 10:43.221
Their hands would be holding their swords out of the water.

10:43.942 --> 10:48.527
And it was like they were saying, Jesus, you can have all of me, but not this.

10:49.829 --> 10:57.838
Because what I do in the kind of, in the battle, what I do in war, that's all down to me and that's what I'm doing.

10:57.939 --> 10:59.801
But you can have every other part of me.

11:01.603 --> 11:04.146
But that's Jesus is not Lord then.

11:04.834 --> 11:11.504
Because Hudson Taylor Missionary to China once said, if he is not Lord of all, he's not Lord at all.

11:11.924 --> 11:13.006
Yeah, something like that.

11:13.026 --> 11:14.067
He'll be behind me, I'm sure.

11:14.448 --> 11:17.853
If he's not Lord of all, he's not Lord at all.

11:18.393 --> 11:24.983
And if Christ is not Lord of everything, he is not Lord of anything because it negates the word Lord.

11:26.505 --> 11:32.914
So Paul is saying to us, if we declare with our mouths that Jesus is

11:33.122 --> 11:39.612
Lord, if we declare with our mouths that Jesus is Lord, that is surrender.

11:41.394 --> 11:44.679
That is saying, I give myself to you.

11:44.739 --> 11:47.844
Full stop.

11:48.685 --> 11:49.646
There's no caveats.

11:50.528 --> 11:53.712
There's no, but not this, but not here, but not when.

11:53.772 --> 11:56.697
It's just I give myself to you.

11:57.217 --> 12:03.026
If you confess or declare with your mouth that Jesus is Lord,

12:03.714 --> 12:08.338
I love the story, and I really connect with this guy in scripture, the story of Thomas.

12:09.440 --> 12:15.025
You know, Thomas was one of the disciples, and he seemed to ask a lot of questions.

12:15.085 --> 12:16.546
There's nothing wrong with asking questions.

12:16.847 --> 12:19.249
Please do not think there's anything wrong with asking questions.

12:19.710 --> 12:25.896
You know, when Jesus rose from the dead, people were coming back and saying, hey, we've seen the Lord, he's risen.

12:26.276 --> 12:29.799
And Thomas was like, yeah, well, I've not seen him.

12:30.700 --> 12:32.562
And maybe he was,

12:32.770 --> 12:36.274
Maybe he was hopeful that he was true, but wasn't quite sure that it happened.

12:36.795 --> 12:39.779
Maybe he was a little bit annoyed that he hadn't met Jesus yet.

12:40.460 --> 12:49.351
We don't know what was happening in him, but he said on one occasion, maybe he was fed up with people saying they'd seen Jesus and he felt left out.

12:49.411 --> 13:01.906
He said, listen, unless I can put my fingers in the palm of his hands where he was nailed to the cross and I can put my fingers in this side where he was stabbed with a spear and in his feet, unless I can touch those wounds,

13:02.370 --> 13:03.391
I'm not believing it.

13:04.673 --> 13:08.077
And then there was a moment where Jesus appears in the room and Thomas is there.

13:08.959 --> 13:11.422
And Jesus, so beautifully, I love what Jesus does.

13:11.462 --> 13:15.948
He says, Thomas says his name, come and put your hands in my wounds.

13:16.448 --> 13:19.112
Because Jesus hears you, let me just say Jesus hears you.

13:19.853 --> 13:22.016
It doesn't matter where you are, Jesus hears you.

13:22.637 --> 13:27.603
And Thomas responds beautifully, Thomas says, my Lord and my God.

13:28.364 --> 13:29.906
There is a moment where Thomas

13:30.114 --> 13:33.959
really fully expresses who Jesus is to him.

13:34.199 --> 13:36.542
He says, my Lord and my God.

13:37.743 --> 13:49.498
And as people who follow Jesus, or maybe people who are thinking about following Jesus, there needs to be a moment where we're able to say, Jesus, you are my Lord and my God.

13:50.359 --> 13:52.521
And if you did that once, that's amazing.

13:52.642 --> 13:55.525
But let me tell you, this needs to be something that happens every day.

13:55.545 --> 13:59.570
Today, Jesus, let me remind myself

13:59.938 --> 14:02.821
that you are my Lord and my God.

14:03.602 --> 14:14.794
Today, Jesus, let me remind myself that regardless of what decisions I have to make, what conversations I get involved in, you are my Lord and my God and I belong to you.

14:14.975 --> 14:19.059
And so what you want is more important than what I want.

14:19.480 --> 14:23.824
What you expect from me is more important than what I expect.

14:24.665 --> 14:28.850
If you declare with your mouth that Jesus is Lord,

14:30.114 --> 14:31.456
and believe in your heart.

14:32.298 --> 14:39.792
So it's not just the declaration, it's not just the stuff that comes out of our mouths, it's the stuff that happens inside of us as well.

14:40.152 --> 14:41.595
Believe in your heart.

14:41.976 --> 14:49.289
And I think maybe historically we're much better at the believing in our hearts bit than the declaring with our mouths bit.

14:49.850 --> 14:54.098
Maybe we're better at, yeah, this is what I feel inside, but I don't want to talk about it.

14:54.530 --> 15:01.299
Or maybe there's some people who talk about a lot of stuff, but actually there's nothing really in terms of depth happening inside.

15:01.980 --> 15:04.864
And I love the way that Paul brings these two things together.

15:04.904 --> 15:13.576
He says, if you declare with your mouth and believe in your heart, declare with your mouth and believe in your heart.

15:14.317 --> 15:17.241
He doesn't just leave a, it's not just a full stop there though.

15:17.321 --> 15:19.144
It's not believe in your heart, end off.

15:19.244 --> 15:20.726
He says, believe in your heart, what?

15:21.247 --> 15:23.730
That God raised him from the dead.

15:24.674 --> 15:30.762
This is the pinnacle, this is the foundation, this is the important thing.

15:30.802 --> 15:35.868
If you had to hang anything, if you had to hang your faith on anything, this is it, the resurrection.

15:36.609 --> 15:44.940
If you had to hang your faith and point your finger at any point in history, point your finger at any point in scripture, it is the resurrection that we hang our faith on.

15:45.460 --> 15:53.010
And Paul is saying, if you confess to the amount of Jesus is the Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

15:53.954 --> 16:00.482
Understanding that Jesus rose from the dead is incredibly important to who we are and what we believe.

16:00.663 --> 16:03.807
Understanding that the resurrection happened is important.

16:03.927 --> 16:08.412
Understanding that the tomb was empty is important to us.

16:09.274 --> 16:10.415
It is important to us.

16:13.579 --> 16:22.130
There are lots of thoughts around the resurrection and there are lots of people who have spent their time and their energy

16:22.370 --> 16:24.152
trying to disprove the resurrection.

16:24.213 --> 16:25.174
And why have they done that?

16:25.274 --> 16:32.865
Because they know that if they can do that, they have kind of mitigated everything that people have said and believed about who Jesus was.

16:33.305 --> 16:34.888
I love that C.S.

16:34.928 --> 16:42.218
Lewis quoted, he was talking about Jesus and he was saying, you can't just say that Jesus should have had the quote, really, but I think I can remember it.

16:42.238 --> 16:45.723
You can't just say that Jesus is a good moral teacher.

16:45.943 --> 16:50.930
You can't say that because a good moral teacher would not say the things that Jesus said.

16:51.106 --> 16:58.578
Jesus said some quite provoking things and quite controversial things, and a good moral teacher would not declare himself to be the son of God.

16:59.259 --> 17:01.402
So don't say Jesus was a good moral teacher.

17:01.823 --> 17:04.587
Either he was who he said he was, or he wasn't.

17:05.168 --> 17:06.971
But you can't say he was a good moral teacher.

17:07.271 --> 17:19.250
In fact, he goes on to say if somebody said those things, he would either be completely nuts, a lunatic, he would be a liar, or he would be Lord, liar, lunatic, or Lord.

17:19.906 --> 17:26.394
And that's how CS Lewis puts the whole idea of what Jesus did on the cross and who Jesus said he was.

17:26.775 --> 17:34.585
He's either a lunatic, he's either a liar or he is Lord, because this is what Jesus said and this is what happened.

17:34.605 --> 17:41.874
But of course over the years there's lots of people who have kind of pointed fingers at the resurrection and said that these things didn't happen.

17:42.498 --> 17:48.283
And there are a few people, there's a guy called Frank Morrison, who wrote a book called Who Rolled a Stone Away, which is a great book.

17:48.383 --> 17:50.265
It's an old book, but it's a great book.

17:50.405 --> 17:56.390
He set out to disprove the resurrection and then found that he couldn't and then wrote a book, Proven the Resurrection, which is great.

17:56.410 --> 17:57.331
I love it when that happens.

17:57.771 --> 18:00.974
There's another guy called Josh McDowell, who wrote a book called Resurrection Factor.

18:01.014 --> 18:01.955
He was a university.

18:02.415 --> 18:04.577
His Christian friends used to really annoy him.

18:04.617 --> 18:08.721
And so he thought, you know, I'm tired of having these conversations with you about Jesus.

18:08.821 --> 18:10.482
I'm going to prove the resurrection didn't happen.

18:10.722 --> 18:12.484
So he did his research.

18:12.464 --> 18:14.487
and couldn't prove that the resurrection didn't happen.

18:14.748 --> 18:17.712
They gave his life to Jesus and then went into ministry, which is great.

18:18.494 --> 18:31.474
There's a guy called Lee Strobel, who was an investigative journalist who, same thing, just wanted to disprove the whole thing to annoy his Christian friends and then went through his own investigation and then came to the point where he thought, actually,

18:31.554 --> 18:32.516
This all makes sense.

18:32.816 --> 18:34.499
And they wrote a book called The Case for Christ.

18:34.880 --> 18:35.861
So I recommend those books.

18:35.881 --> 18:36.663
They're really good books.

18:36.683 --> 18:37.524
I recommend those books.

18:37.905 --> 18:39.427
But let me just point out a few things.

18:39.668 --> 18:46.640
Let me just point out a few things about the resurrection, because the resurrection is quite important to us as people who follow Jesus.

18:47.140 --> 18:51.047
Some of the things that people have said are it was the tomb was unknown.

18:51.668 --> 18:52.850
It was an unknown tomb.

18:53.154 --> 19:05.987
that they put Jesus' body somewhere after his crucifixion, and then the disciples had no idea where Jesus was, and they just made up stories that he'd been raised from the dead, which is nonsense because we know that Jesus actually was in a borrowed tomb.

19:06.208 --> 19:10.098
We know someone's name, Joseph of Arimathea, Lent.

19:10.210 --> 19:11.392
lent someone your tomb.

19:11.472 --> 19:12.814
It's a bit of a weird concept, isn't it?

19:12.974 --> 19:15.438
But that's what they did, lent Jesus his tomb.

19:15.458 --> 19:16.820
So we know where the tomb was.

19:17.241 --> 19:22.509
And if it was the wrong tomb or they didn't know where the tomb was, this is another theory.

19:22.649 --> 19:27.736
When the women returned on Sunday to honor Christ, they went to the wrong tomb and it was empty and thought, oh, Jesus is risen.

19:28.337 --> 19:34.066
But that means that everybody after that point also went to the wrong tomb, which doesn't make any sense.

19:34.146 --> 19:40.295
There are other things that this is just a legend that people made up after Jesus had died and decayed.

19:40.335 --> 19:41.597
They just made the legend up.

19:41.998 --> 19:46.645
But 1 Corinthians 15 verse 6 says, at one point Jesus appeared to 500 people.

19:47.506 --> 19:51.332
That's not legend, that Jesus appeared to 500 people.

19:53.214 --> 19:55.698
There's another one that says it was a...

19:56.130 --> 19:58.153
It was a spiritual resurrection, I love these.

19:58.353 --> 19:59.695
It was a spiritual resurrection.

19:59.875 --> 20:04.021
Jesus' body decayed in the grave and that his real resurrection was spiritual.

20:04.903 --> 20:08.908
No, because he appeared to more than 500 people at one time afterwards, so no.

20:09.469 --> 20:12.754
There's another one that said people who saw Jesus afterwards were hallucinating.

20:13.355 --> 20:17.040
No, because 500 people do not have the same hallucination.

20:17.100 --> 20:20.945
That's not how hallucinations work.

20:21.025 --> 20:24.210
There's another one that said his bodies were stolen by the disciples.

20:25.698 --> 20:28.181
This is my favorite, it's not my favorite, second favorite one.

20:28.481 --> 20:30.243
The body was stolen by the disciples.

20:31.064 --> 20:35.949
For his body to be stolen by the disciples and the disciples made stories up about Jesus being resurrected.

20:36.649 --> 20:41.975
They would have to roll the stone away, but before they could roll the stone away, remember what they would have to do?

20:42.475 --> 20:43.877
Get through the Roman guard.

20:44.277 --> 20:45.979
There were Roman soldiers guarding the tomb.

20:46.519 --> 20:50.203
That would have lasted six seconds and it would not have gone in their favor.

20:50.764 --> 20:52.946
Yeah, you do not mess with the Roman soldiers.

20:53.218 --> 20:54.019
They were fishermen.

20:54.179 --> 20:57.723
They were not skilled in, you know, Jewish arts.

20:58.003 --> 21:00.026
I was going to say martial arts.

21:00.046 --> 21:01.027
Jewish martial arts.

21:01.347 --> 21:02.749
They were not skilled in these things.

21:02.789 --> 21:05.692
They would not have stood a chance against the Roman soldiers.

21:06.473 --> 21:08.736
So that doesn't make any sense.

21:08.756 --> 21:17.085
And if that happened, then why would Pilate have said to the guards, hey guys, yeah, we know that the body is gone, the stones have been rolled away.

21:17.526 --> 21:18.827
This is what you are to say.

21:18.887 --> 21:21.330
This is what you are to say.

21:21.442 --> 21:25.748
The authorities told the soldiers what to say.

21:25.788 --> 21:29.373
The authorities told the soldiers what to say after Jesus had risen from the dead.

21:30.615 --> 21:30.975
Two more.

21:31.496 --> 21:38.786
One is that the authorities moved Jesus' body to a safe place so they could be sure that no one would make stories up about his resurrection.

21:39.146 --> 21:39.827
Doesn't make sense.

21:40.048 --> 21:42.931
Why would they do something that was the cause of all of their problems?

21:43.332 --> 21:44.253
Oh, his body's not there.

21:44.373 --> 21:44.854
He's raised.

21:45.134 --> 21:46.837
Actually, they would just say, actually, no, here it is.

21:47.578 --> 21:48.619
But doesn't make any sense.

21:48.960 --> 21:50.642
This is my absolute favorite.

21:52.162 --> 21:56.146
There's a theory that says that Jesus didn't die, he fainted.

21:58.508 --> 22:10.980
And then, because the tomb was cool, he came back to himself, he rolled the stone away, he fought off the guards, and then appeared to his disciples as Lord of life.

22:11.701 --> 22:21.010
That is almost more miraculous than Jesus raising from the dead, almost more miraculous.

22:21.346 --> 22:23.268
The resurrection is really important to us.

22:23.969 --> 22:25.250
It is really important to us.

22:25.791 --> 22:37.183
And as people who are followers of Jesus, we've got to this point because we have declared that Jesus is Lord and we've believed in our hearts that He raised Him from the dead.

22:37.864 --> 22:39.546
That is important.

22:39.566 --> 22:41.488
It is important.

22:41.508 --> 22:47.154
You know, one of my, one of the things that I do in the summer, people say, Nick, you're a teacher, you have so much holiday.

22:47.234 --> 22:53.693
No, I do not have so much holiday and don't bring it up because it's annoying because I go back to work on the 16th of August.

22:53.914 --> 22:54.977
That is not a lot of holiday.

22:55.197 --> 22:57.083
All right, I go back to work in the middle of August.

22:57.544 --> 23:02.258
One of the things that we have to go back to work in the middle of August for college lecturers is enrollment.

23:02.498 --> 23:06.624
Yeah, all of the students gather GCSEs and their A-level results, and then they come to enroll.

23:06.984 --> 23:12.713
And what the college could do is, I'll cut this out, what the college could do is they could employ other people to do their homework.

23:12.793 --> 23:15.557
But no, we got the lecturers back in.

23:15.657 --> 23:17.459
They can do some extra work in the summer.

23:17.900 --> 23:22.066
So we get, actually, it's a good idea, because if parents bring the students in and they want to ask,

23:22.146 --> 23:26.452
questions about the courses, the people who teach the courses are the best people to answer those questions.

23:26.772 --> 23:27.373
So I get it.

23:27.974 --> 23:33.442
So what we have to do is we have to sit at the desk and then students are coming in and they're saying, these are my grades.

23:33.502 --> 23:34.603
Can I come and do the course?

23:35.064 --> 23:39.290
And we can look at the grades and we can say, yes, you can do the course or no, you cannot do the course.

23:39.590 --> 23:45.038
And the reason we can do that is because each course has been set up with something called entry requirements.

23:45.478 --> 23:48.362
They are lifesavers, entry requirements.

23:48.803 --> 23:51.026
Because it's a bit mean to say to someone,

23:51.234 --> 23:52.235
No, you can't do the course.

23:52.735 --> 23:53.056
Sorry.

23:53.516 --> 23:57.160
And then not have a reason to say you can't do the course.

23:57.220 --> 23:57.980
I don't like the way you look.

23:58.000 --> 23:58.801
You can't do the course.

23:59.402 --> 24:01.944
You have to have a reason to say you can't do this course.

24:02.024 --> 24:03.205
This course is not for you.

24:03.546 --> 24:06.008
And the reason is the entry requirements.

24:06.028 --> 24:09.311
You do not have five GCSEs, grade nine to four.

24:09.892 --> 24:11.313
So you can't do the course.

24:11.573 --> 24:12.054
I'm sorry.

24:12.154 --> 24:13.855
But here's something else is always something else.

24:14.136 --> 24:15.317
Here's something else you could do.

24:15.517 --> 24:16.118
Yeah.

24:16.138 --> 24:18.560
So entry requirements are quite important.

24:19.781 --> 24:20.722
This verse

24:20.962 --> 24:47.730
is a great verse because it says, if you declare with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart, it does not say, if you are good, if you behave yourself, if you've never said anything or done anything wrong, if you were born in a particular place, if you were bright, if you've been to Bible college, if you attend church regularly,

24:48.258 --> 24:50.582
If you serve, it should say if you serve.

24:50.602 --> 24:51.143
If it doesn't.

24:51.684 --> 24:56.251
If you serve, it doesn't say any of those things.

24:57.413 --> 24:59.536
There are no entry requirements.

25:00.438 --> 25:08.511
The only entry requirement to be someone who enters into and experiences the salvation that Jesus won for us.

25:08.811 --> 25:12.637
The only requirement is that you accept it.

25:12.657 --> 25:13.138
That's it.

25:13.730 --> 25:17.515
That's the only requirement that you accept what Jesus has already done.

25:17.815 --> 25:20.038
There are no entry requirements.

25:20.619 --> 25:26.807
All we have to do is declare with our mouths and believe in our heart.

25:27.628 --> 25:33.896
All we have to do is declare with our mouths and believe in our heart and accept what Jesus has done.

25:34.917 --> 25:35.858
That's all we have to do.

25:37.721 --> 25:39.183
So I want to close in prayer.

25:40.164 --> 25:41.906
So I just want you to bow your heads for a moment.

25:43.522 --> 25:56.135
Paul makes it very clear.

25:56.196 --> 26:00.240
There's a very, very simple thing for us to do.

26:04.164 --> 26:09.289
We have to confess with our mouths and we have to believe in our hearts.

26:09.309 --> 26:09.810
That is it.

26:11.586 --> 26:13.808
And maybe you've done this and that's really good.

26:14.489 --> 26:18.033
But maybe you haven't done it and there's an opportunity for you to do that today.

26:19.875 --> 26:40.498
And so I want you to just in the quiet with your eyes closed, just to think this incredible gift of salvation that Jesus won for us is free.

26:42.050 --> 26:42.991
But it wasn't cheap.

26:46.397 --> 26:51.284
Jesus gave his life for us to be able to experience the salvation.

26:53.568 --> 26:55.050
But the promise is very simple.

26:56.032 --> 27:05.326
If you declare with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

27:07.069 --> 27:10.194
Maybe for some of us, it's a bit of reassurance today.

27:12.450 --> 27:15.675
Maybe we just need to be reminded of how simple the gospel is.

27:16.756 --> 27:20.742
Maybe you did that a long time ago and you've slipped into trying really hard.

27:23.226 --> 27:24.868
And there's nothing wrong with trying really hard.

27:26.010 --> 27:29.014
But it doesn't impact on your salvation because your salvation is free.

27:35.543 --> 27:37.286
I saw a lot of pray for my friends in this room.

27:39.009 --> 27:40.050
I pray that

27:40.194 --> 27:46.323
we would have a revelation, a fresh understanding of who you are and what you have done for us.

27:47.625 --> 28:05.591
And thank you for the simplicity of the gospel that it is just declaring that you are Lord, recognizing who you are and saying that yes, you are Lord, you are master, you are ruler over us and believing that you raised from the dead in our hearts.

28:06.572 --> 28:07.794
I pray that

28:07.906 --> 28:13.635
Maybe for those of us who haven't made those connections, I pray that there would be a connection between what we say and what we believe.

28:13.735 --> 28:14.597
Help us, Jesus.

28:15.558 --> 28:28.479
Maybe for those of us who do believe, but a little bit nervous about saying it out loud, I pray you give us boldness, that in those moments where we have an opportunity to talk about you and to talk about what you've done in us, that we would not shy away from those moments.

28:29.481 --> 28:32.786
And I pray, Jesus, that you help us to live in that space

28:32.866 --> 28:50.285
of confessing with our mouth, declaring with our mouth and believing in our hearts to live in that space so that we know that we are saved, so that we know who's we are, and so that we can truly declare that you are Lord of us.

28:52.667 --> 28:58.354
Help us, I pray, in Jesus' name.

28:58.374 --> 28:58.474
Amen.

28:58.494 --> 28:59.995
We've come to the end of this week's message.

29:00.596 --> 29:02.418
We hope you've been impacted and inspired.

29:03.010 --> 29:09.874
Please keep up to date with everything that's happening by visiting our website at www.livechurchgoingsin.com

